<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 15 at 1:50AM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of central Craig County
through 230 AM CDT...
At 150 AM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 6 miles
north of White Oak, moving northeast at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects
is possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Vinita...                         Welch...
Bluejacket...                     White Oak...
Pyramid Corners...                Centrailia...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
